description: Number of distinct parameter sets (v,k,lambda) for Abelian difference sets of order n = k-lambda with 1 <= lambda <= n-1.
references: D. Jungnickel, Difference Sets, Chapter 7 of J. H. Dinitz and D R. Stinson, Contemporary Design Theory, Wiley, 1992, see Appendix.
example: The 3 parameter sets for order 4 are (v,k,lambda) = (21,5,1), (16,6,2) and (15,7,3).
author: _N. J. A. Sloane_, Jan 17 2000
